Tanzania’s Mines Minister Says Companies Agree to 4% Royalty

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-10-19T12:23:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/tanzania-s-mines-minister-says-companies-agree-to-4-royalty.html
Tanzania’s mines ministry and
companies operating in the country have agreed to a royalty rate
of 4 percent, up from the current 3 percent, William Ngeleja,
the country’s minister of energy and minerals, told reporters in
Arusha today.  The new royalty will be imposed this year, he said.  “We have basically reached an agreement with the mining
companies on the matter,” he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in Dar es Salaam at 
 dmalingha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
